---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Identity Stem | Identity Engineering">
	<main class="min-h-screen">
		<!-- Header -->
		<section class="pt-24 pb-16 px-6 border-b border-white/10">
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
				<div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-violet-400/70 mb-4">Core Concept</div>
				<h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6">
					Identity Stem
				</h1>
				<p class="text-xl text-white/50 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
					The directed axis through spacetime. The geometric core around which substance rotates with minimal wobble — the Schwerachse of identity.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Three Temporal Domains -->
		<section class="py-24 px-6">
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-32">

				<!-- Past -->
				<div>
					<div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-cyan-400/70 mb-3">01 — Past</div>
					<h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-6">State Differential</h2>
					<p class="text-lg text-white/60 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						The observed derivative of the state: <code class="text-violet-300">δS = dS/dt</code> (or discrete ΔS).
						This is the causal chain of actual changes from the past up to the present moment.
					</p>
					<p class="text-lg text-white/60 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						It maximizes <strong class="text-white/80">Sameness-as-Trajectory</strong>.
						Recognizability after change does not come from the current snapshot (which is copyable),
						but from the transparent history of how the identity has moved.
					</p>
					<p class="text-lg text-white/60 leading-relaxed">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Engineering task:</strong> Make the State Differential transparent and owned.
						The past is not a fixed story to defend, but a verifiable causal chain that authenticates the entity even after radical change.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- Present -->
				<div>
					<div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-violet-400/70 mb-3">02 — Present</div>
					<h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-6">State</h2>
					<p class="text-lg text-white/60 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						<code class="text-violet-300">S(t)</code> — the high-dimensional state vector at the current moment
						(competencies, relationships, inner states, positions, resources…).
					</p>
					<p class="text-lg text-white/60 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						The present is only the <strong class="text-white/80">current cross-section</strong> of the Stem.
						It is necessary as the meeting point of past trajectory and future gradient, but it is never the full definition of identity.
					</p>
					<p class="text-lg text-white/60 leading-relaxed">
						<strong class="text-white/80">State ≠ Identity.</strong>
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- Future -->
				<div>
					<div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-cyan-400/70 mb-3">03 — Future</div>
					<h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-6">Vision Gradient</h2>
					<p class="text-lg text-white/60 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						<code class="text-violet-300">V ≈ ∇𝒞</code> where 𝒞 is causal entropy (the measure of future freedom of action).
					</p>

					<div class="bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-8">
						<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-white/90">The Gradient — The Best Step Upward</h3>
						<ul class="space-y-3 text-white/60">
							<li class="flex gap-3">
								<span class="text-violet-400">→</span>
								<span>It shows you, at every point of a mathematical landscape, the exact direction of the <strong class="text-white/80">steepest ascent</strong>.</span>
							</li>
							<li class="flex gap-3">
								<span class="text-violet-400">→</span>
								<span>Not a number, but an arrow (vector): direction for the next step + steepness (how strongly the value changes).</span>
							</li>
							<li class="flex gap-3">
								<span class="text-violet-400">→</span>
								<span>Local and short-sighted: it leads step by step to the nearest hill (local maximum).</span>
							</li>
							<li class="flex gap-3">
								<span class="text-violet-400">→</span>
								<span>The tool of AI: when reversed (gradient descent), it reliably leads downhill to minimize error and train models.</span>
							</li>
						</ul>
					</div>

					<p class="text-lg text-white/60 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						In Identity Engineering, <strong class="text-white/80">Vision is the intended gradient of causal entropy</strong>.
						It points in the direction in configuration space where future freedom of action increases most steeply.
					</p>
					<p class="text-lg text-white/60 leading-relaxed">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Engineering task:</strong> Sharpen the Vision Gradient. Make the direction of steepest ascent of freedom clear, strong, and owned.
					</p>
				</div>

			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Integration -->
		<section class="py-24 px-6 border-t border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02]">
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
				<div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-violet-400/70 mb-4">Integration</div>
				<h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8">The Full Stem</h2>

				<p class="text-lg text-white/60 leading-relaxed mb-8">
					Identity (the complete Schwerachse) is the <strong class="text-white/80">integrated Worldline</strong> that holds both forces in productive tension:
				</p>

				<ul class="space-y-4 text-lg text-white/60 mb-12">
					<li class="flex gap-3">
						<span class="text-cyan-400">←</span>
						<span><strong class="text-white/80">Backward:</strong> State Differential → Sameness-as-Trajectory</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex gap-3">
						<span class="text-violet-400">→</span>
						<span><strong class="text-white/80">Forward:</strong> Vision Gradient → Causal Entropy</span>
					</li>
				</ul>

				<div class="bg-black/40 border border-white/10 rounded-2xl p-8 font-mono text-sm text-violet-200/90 overflow-x-auto mb-12">
					I = arg max_γ [ ∫<sub>now</sub><sup>future</sup> V(γ(t)) · dγ  +  consistency with past State Differential ]
				</div>

				<p class="text-lg text-white/60 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					The <strong class="text-white/80">Integral of the Vision</strong> is the line integral of the gradient along the trajectory.
					It equals the cumulative gain in future freedom of action realized by that path.
				</p>

				<p class="text-lg text-white/60 leading-relaxed">
					Identity Engineering works on exactly two primary levers:
				</p>
				<ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-3 text-lg text-white/60 mt-4 ml-2">
					<li>Transparency and ownership of the <strong class="text-white/80">State Differential</strong> (make the past visible and owned).</li>
					<li>Clarity and force of the <strong class="text-white/80">Vision Gradient</strong> (define the direction of steepest ascent of freedom).</li>
				</ol>

				<p class="text-lg text-white/60 leading-relaxed mt-8">
					The result is a Stem with high rotational stability (little wobble) and simultaneously high causal entropy (open future).
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Why it matters -->
		<section class="py-24 px-6 border-t border-white/10">
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
				<h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Why this matters in the AI era</h2>
				<p class="text-lg text-white/60 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					Static snapshots of identity become cheap and copyable.
					What remains authentic is the <strong class="text-white/80">signed history of differentials</strong> that starts from a unique human origin and continues through freedom-maximizing updates.
				</p>
				<p class="text-lg text-white/60 leading-relaxed">
					Observation of change itself constitutes ongoing identity.
					The Identity Stem is therefore both the personal core and the foundation for future-proof, non-copyable identity systems.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Back -->
		<section class="py-16 px-6 border-t border-white/10">
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
				<a href="/" class="text-white/40 hover:text-white/70 transition text-sm uppercase tracking-widest">
					← Back to Framework
				</a>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	code {
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
		background: rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
		padding: 0.15em 0.4em;
		border-radius: 4px;
		font-size: 0.9em;
	}
</style>
